properties.Name: ExperianConsumerName
properties.Description:
The credit report lists all of the name variations reported to Experian by your creditors, including nicknames or middle names. 

By maintaining those names, Experian is able to match them to any accounts that may not have been converted yet to your current name by your lenders and include them in the credit report.

Columns.Name: ExperianReportNumber
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Experian consumer.

Columns.Name: NameId
Columns.Description: The name identification number is used to identify which accounts are associated with each individual name variation.
